<p>PerlMonksFlair was developed lovingly by 
<a href="http://www.gideondsouza.com/">Gideon Israel Dsouza</a> 
and designed graciously by <a href="http://jenniferleigh.ca/">Jennifer Leigh Holt</a>. I built it with <a href='http://www.perl.org/'>Perl</a>, <a href='https://www.varnish-cache.org/'>Varnish</a>, <a href='http://www.perldancer.org/'>Dancer</a> and <a href='https://metacpan.org/module/Starman'>Starman</a></p>

<p>If you haven't figured it out yet, it is a simple flair generator for users on <a href="http://perlmonks.org/">perlmonks.org</a>.
</p>

<p>All you have to do is stick the following url into your site, blog, where ever you like and a pretty badge will display, showing off your achievements in perlmonks.org</p>

<blockquote>http://www.perlmonksflair.com/<strong>your_username_on_perlmonks</strong>.jpg</blockquote>

<p>Here is what my flair looks like:<p/>
<a href='http://perlmonks.org/?node=gideondsouza'><img src='http://www.perlmonksflair.com/gideondsouza.jpg' alt="gideondsouza on perlmonks.org" class="img-polaroid"></a>

<p><strong>Note:</strong> Generated Images are cached for 5 days. Suggestions, Feedback, Issues and Insults: <a href='https://github.com/gideondsouza/perlmonksflair/' class='btn btn-primary'>Goto Github Project</a></p>

